       r2.id AS reaction2_id, r2.name AS reaction2_name,

- **R03778** – octanoyl‑CoA:acetyl‑CoA C‑acyltransferase  
- **R03858** – lauroyl‑CoA:acetyl‑CoA C‑acyltransferase

**Pathway: Fatty Acid Biosynthesis (path:gmx00061)**  
- **Species:** GMX  
- **Source:** KEGG  
- **Title:** Fatty acid biosynthesis  

**Key Details**

- **Pathway image:** https://www.kegg.jp/kegg/pathway/gmx/gmx00061.png  

**Main Reactions Involved**  
The pathway includes a series of enzymatic steps that synthesize fatty acids. Some of the reactions are:  
- (3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein] hydro‑lyase  
- acyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein]:NADP⁺ oxidoreductase  
- acyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein]:NAD⁺ oxidoreductase  
- long‑chain‑fatty‑acid:CoA ligase (AMP‑forming)  
- long‑chain acyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- (3R)-3‑hydroxyacyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein]:NADP⁺ oxidoreductase  
- (3R)-3‑hydroxyacyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein]:NAD⁺ oxidoreductase  
- acyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein]:malonyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein] C‑acyltransferase (decarboxylating)  
- malonate:CoA ligase (AMP‑forming)  
- palmitate:CoA ligase (AMP‑forming)  
- (3R)-3‑hydroxypalmitoyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein] hydro‑lyase  
- dodecanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein] hydrolase  
- hexadecenoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- decanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- octanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- stearoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein], reduced‑ferredoxin:oxygen oxidoreductase (9,10 cis‑dehydrogenating)  
- octadecanoyl‑[acp]:NAD⁺ trans‑2‑oxidoreductase  
- hexadecanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein], reduced‑ferredoxin:oxygen oxidoreductase (9,10 cis‑dehydrogenating)  
- octadecanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- oleoyl‑[acyl‑carrier‑protein] hydrolase  
- tetradecanoyl‑[acyl‑carrier protein] hydrolase  
- ... (and many more reactions listed in the pathway)

**Functional Units**  
- ko:K13370  

This pathway describes the enzymatic processes that build fatty acids in the GMX organism, detailing the conversion of acetyl‑CoA and malonyl‑CoA into long‑chain fatty acids through a series of condensation, reduction, dehydration, and trans‑esterification steps.
